    "description": "NKK Switches Co., Ltd. engages in the development, manufacture, and sale of various switches for industrial. It operates through Japan, Europe and the United States, and Asia segments. It offers toggle, rocker, pushbutton, illuminated pushbutton, multi-function pushbutton, emergency stop, key lock, rotary, slide, tactile, and tilt switches; indicator lights; relays; sheet keyboards; touch panels; and accessories, as well as universal design products. The company's products are used in information and communication equipment, space satellite equipment, computers, FA automation equipment, aviation, railways, ships, medical care, disaster prevention, measurement and control equipment, semiconductor-related equipment, amusement, mobile communication, health and environment, and other fields. The company was formerly known as Nihon Kaiheiki Ind. Co., Ltd. and changed its name to NKK Switches Co., Ltd. in April 2014. NKK Switches Co., Ltd. was founded in 1951 and is headquartered in Kawasaki, Japan."
